(cos\theta - sec \theta)^2=\tan^{2}\left(\theta\right)-\sin^{2}\left(\theta\right)
 \left(\cos\theta -\frac{1}{\cos\theta}\right)^2 =  \left(\frac{\cos^2\theta - 1}{\cos\theta}\right)^2  =\left(\frac{-\sin^2\theta }{\cos\theta}\right)^2 \\ =\left(\frac{\sin^4\theta }{\cos^2\theta}\right)   =\left(\frac{\sin^2\theta \left[1-\cos^2\theta\right]}{\cos^2\theta}\right)   =\tan^2\theta -\sin^2\theta 
(\cos\theta-\sec\theta)^2=\cos^2\theta-2+\sec^2\theta=(\sec^2\theta-1)-(1-\cos^2\theta)=\tan^2\theta-\sin^2\theta
 -1 = \tan^2\theta -\sec^2\theta = \cos^2\theta + \sin^2\theta -2 
 \tan^2\theta - \sin^2\theta = \cos^2\theta -2 + \sec^2\theta \\ = \cos^2\theta -2\cos\theta\sec\theta + \sec^2\theta \\ =(\cos\theta-\sec\theta)^2  
